    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small deep sea worm-like mollusks lacking calcareous plates on the body but having fine slimy spicules on the covering mantle and known as narrow-footed gliders. In some classifications, this division, along with "Caudofauveata" is called a class instead of a subclass; here the two are combined under class "Aplacophora."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
